    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60D/100½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-21">October 21,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>The Minister<note n="42" xml:id="d96fn42">Hjalmar J. Procopé, Minister of
                        Finland.</note> asked me if I could make any statement to him with regard to
                    the relations between Finland and the United States which would relieve his mind
                    in view of his approaching confinement to the hospital. I said that there were
                    no developments since I had previously talked with the Minister and that the
                    situation still remained on a 24-hour basis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
